he daemon inbox (`/run/cypherclaw-tmp/inbox.jsonl`). The daemon (2750-line `src/cypherclaw/daemon.py`) routes messages through Claude/Gemini/Codex with conversation memory, budget management, and smart routing. Responses come back via a shared message bus (`/tmp/cypherclaw_messages.jsonl`) that the face reads.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**What's on the face:**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Typing** — just start typing, no toggle. Words appear right-aligned below the face.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Responses** — daemon responses float left-aligned (blue). Same agents as Telegram.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Telegram mirror** — daemon's `tg_send()` patched to also write to face bus. Everything sent to Telegram shows on the face.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **System events** — key changes, mood shifts, art generation, Theramini activity appear centered in amber.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Thinking animation** — orbiting particles, expanding ripples, and LLM-generated musings (qwen3.5:4b) while waiting for daemon response.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Chat history** — Tab toggles scrollable history from daemon conversation memory.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Emoji stripping** — PIL can't render emoji, so they're stripped from bus messages.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Key files on CypherClaw:**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `/home/user/cypherclaw/tools/senseweave/keyboard_chat.py` — face terminal module\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `/home/user/cypherclaw/tools/face_display.py` — patched: calls `chat.poll_system()`, `chat.poll_message_bus()`, `chat.render()`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `/home/user/cypherclaw/src/cypherclaw/daemon.py` — patched: `_face_bus()` mirrors `tg_send()` to message bus\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### 2. Audio Fixes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Disconnected webcam + Scarlett inputs from SuperCollider (caused occasional pops via USB audio glitches)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Commented out input connections in `scripts/start_audio.sh` so they don't return on reboot\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Inputs should be reconnected only when Theramini duet or contact mic listener is ready\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### 3. Artist's Plan Completion PRD\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-New PRD (`prd-artist-plan-completion.md`) with 14 requirements covering gaps:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **APC-001--005:** Visitor identity (face recognition, person registry, greeting)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **APC-006--009:** Physical output (fix printer, sound postcards, daily digest, welcome stickers)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **APC-010--011:** Gallery exhibition mode (curated sequences)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **APC-012--013:** Room acoustics (swept sine IR, convolution reverb SynthDef)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **APC-014:** B&P color covers via DreamShaper\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### 4. Artist's Plan Rectified\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Updated `artist-plan.md`: PipeWire not JACK, 21 chars not 15, Pareidolia not GlyphWeave, added Inner Life section, marked phase completion percentages, cross-referenced covering PRDs.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### 5. R750 Ollama Integration (built by local SDP pipeline)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-12 tasks completed (all PASS), building the code for R750 deployment:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `ollama_health.py` — health check + model listing for dual-socket Ollama\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `federation/discovery.py` — Tailscale peer discovery with registry merge\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `cypherclaw_daemon.py` — `_invoke_ollama()` HTTP invoke, `run_agent()` Ollama branch, `LOCAL_ONLY` mode, `_available_agents()` respects health + quota\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `quota_monitor.py` — local provider infinite headroom, Ollama models in PROVIDERS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `first_boot.py` — instance identity with artistic name generation (already existed on CypherClaw)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- 11 new test files covering all Ollama integration paths\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### 6. CypherClaw Day 1-4 Build Committed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-64 files (11,907 insertions) committed on CypherClaw and synced to PromptClaw repo. This was the entire Day 1-4 build that was sitting uncommitted.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Pipeline State\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### CypherClaw SDP\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **531 total tasks, 434 complete (82%)**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Runner active (`sdp-cli run --force`)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- 32 pending, 55 needs_split, 9 blocked, 84 skipped\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- ETA ~7 hours (2 AM tomorrow)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Loaded PRDs: artist-plan-completion (14 tasks), embodiment-core (13), embodiment-interaction-loops (12), clone (14), identity (9), federation-read (9), federation-writes (7), bundle-exchange (8), publication (10)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### Local MacBook SDP\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **14/14 complete (100%)** — R750 Ollama integration\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Runner stopped (work is done)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- R750 PRD: `my-claw/sdp/prd-r750-ollama-integration.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Running Services on CypherClaw\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `scsynth` (PipeWire, port 57110)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `duet_composer.py` (music with Korsakov Ch.1-4)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `face_display.py` (face terminal + chat)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `cypherclaw daemon` (Telegram bot, multi-agent routing)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `sdp-cli run` (SDP pipeline runner)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Art engine, gallery, web gallery, all sensor daemons\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**NOT running:**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `telegram_commands.py` — killed because it conflicted with daemon (409 errors). The daemon handles all Telegram.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Inner life loop — was built but not started this session (needs to be added to boot script)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## What Needs Attention\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### Immediate\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-1. **Start inner life loop on CypherClaw** — `tools/inner_life/main.py` is built but not in the boot script or running as a daemon\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-2. **telegram_commands.py keeps respawning** — it was killed but something may restart it. Check if a systemd unit or cron is respawning it. The daemon handles Telegram — telegram_commands should stay disabled.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-3. **Face display sometimes has two processes** — kill both and restart one cleanly\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-4. **APC-010/011 need_split** — gallery exhibition tasks flagged as too broad, the pipeline will auto-split them\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### R750 Deployment\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-The integration code is built and tested. When deploying:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-1. Complete bare metal runbook (`docs/r750-bare-metal-runbook.md`)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-2. Run model evaluation plan (`docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md`)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-3. Update model names in `OLLAMA_MODELS` routing config (currently placeholders)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-4. SCP the modified files to R750\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-5. Set `LOCAL_ONLY=true` in `.env` for full local inference mode\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### Keyboard Chat on CypherClaw\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-The face terminal is working but could use:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Better font rendering (consider rendering text to a separate surface for anti-aliasing)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- The `expression_override` property exists on `KeyboardChat` — wire it into `face_display.py` so the face goes \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"curious\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" while thinking\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Long daemon responses get cut off — consider word-wrapping at render time (already implemented but test with real long responses)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Key Architectural Decisions Made This Session\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-1. **Face is a thin client** — no LLM calls, no Telegram polling. All intelligence goes through the daemon. The daemon is the single source of truth for conversation.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-2. **Message bus pattern** — JSONL append files for inter-process communication. Simple, atomic, no dependencies.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-3. **Thinking animation uses local LLM** — qwen3.5:4b generates contextual musings while the real agents work. Nice UX, trivial cost.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-4. **Two pipelines in parallel** — CypherClaw runs the main task queue, MacBook runs R750 prep. Different PRDs, different queues, same codebase.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Git State\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **PromptClaw** (MacBook): `feat/graceful-degradation` branch, pushed to GitHub\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **CypherClaw**: `agent/t1/demo-day-caveats` branch, pushed to cypherclaw-private\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- These are different repos (`exquest/PromptClaw` vs `exquest/cypherclaw-private`) with overlapping content under different directory structures (`my-claw/tools/` vs `tools/`)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# Progress\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+Generated from SQLite state (`tasks`, `task_runs`, `escalations`). Do not edit manually.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ETC: ~3h 45m remaining (24 tasks, low confidence, calibrating)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+Expected completion: 1:39 AM tomorrow.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+Progress: [███████████████░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░] 38%  15 / 39 tasks complete\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  completed: 15, pending: 24, blocked: 0, skipped: 1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-001@20260408T223256Z**: complete — Completed with verdict PASS WITH NOTES.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-002@20260408T223256Z**: complete — Completed with verdict PASS WITH NOTES.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-003@20260408T223256Z**: complete — Completed with verdict PASS.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-004@20260408T223256Z**: complete — Completed with verdict PASS.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-005@20260408T223256Z**: complete — Completed with verdict PASS.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-006@20260408T223256Z**: complete — Completed with verdict PASS.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-007@20260408T223256Z**: complete — Completed with verdict PASS.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-008@20260408T223256Z**: complete — Completed with verdict PASS WITH NOTES.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-009@20260408T223256Z**: complete — Completed with verdict PASS.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-010@20260408T223256Z**: split — Split into subtasks.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-0