CHANGELOG.md:233:- Added depth-2 generation cache end-to-end test coverage (frac-0075): `tests/test_generation_cache.py` now includes `GenerationCacheEndToEndTests`, which drives the public `GenerationCache` API through the full miss → put → hit → replace cycle (asserting content-addressed filenames, suffix preservation, accessed-at LRU updates, and in-place byte replacement), the queue/storage `set`/`get` aliases sharing a single on-disk entry with `put`/`lookup`, a JSON-safe index round-trip via `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`, a multi-entry restart that recovers surviving entries while pruning a payload deleted out-of-band, and a combined count + size LRU cap where an explicit lookup keeps the oldest entry warm and forces eviction of the middle entry. `tests/test_test_generation_cache_depth.py` pins `tests/test_generation_cache.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing per-function generation cache assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/cache.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4504 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
