CHANGELOG.md:273:- Added depth-2 end-to-end accompaniment test coverage (frac-0055): `tests/test_accompaniment.py` now ships a new `TestAccompanimentEndToEnd` class that drives the existing Korsakov accompaniment public surface (`DensityTracker`, `select_accompaniment_type`, `breathing_swell`, `should_transition_gradually`, `should_pedal`, `pedal_note`, `get_pattern`, and the six pattern generators) through end-to-end multi-step pytest methods. The new tests sweep the documented density bands and verify the inverse-density rule, iterate every pattern type 1-6 to assert non-empty events with positive amps/releases, sweep `breathing_swell` over rest/active/edge inputs, walk full phrase boundaries through `should_pedal` + `pedal_note`, run the dense-melody and resting-melody pipelines end-to-end through a synthetic `DensityTracker` window, and pin a six-bar composer loop. A `test_test_accompaniment_reaches_depth_two` gate test asserts the file's fractal classification is at least depth 2. Existing `TestDensityTracker`, `TestSelectAccompanimentType`, `TestPatterns`, `TestPedalPoint`, `TestBreathing`, and `TestTransition` assertions are preserved unchanged; `tests/test_accompaniment_depth.py`, `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py`, and the startup identity anchors remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:275:- Added depth-2 pytest collection gate reports (frac-0054): `tests/conftest.py` now exposes a frozen `CollectionGateDecision` dataclass plus `collection_gate_decisions`, `apply_collection_gate_decisions`, and `summarize_collection_gate_decisions` so tests and diagnostics can inspect live/host-specific marker gates with enabled state, skip reason, matched count, skipped count, and JSON-safe totals. Existing `--run-live-modal`, `--run-live-replicate`, `live_modal`, `live_replicate`, and `cypherclaw_e2e` behavior is preserved: Modal/Replicate live tests skip by default unless opted in, and CypherClaw e2e skips on CI. `tests/test_conftest_depth.py` pins hook registration, default and CI gate behavior, JSON-safe summaries, and fractal depth >= 2; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:293:- Added depth-2 hook schema rewriter (frac-0044): `rewrite_hook.py` is now an importable module with a frozen `HookRewriteResult` dataclass plus typed helpers `apply_field_renames`, `migrate_file`, `apply_hook_rewrites`, and `main`, sourced from a canonical `HOOK_FIELD_RENAMES` table (`("hook_type", "hook_class")`, `("rhythm_cell", "rhythm")`) and `HOOK_TARGET_FILES` listing the five SenseWeave files the original one-shot script wrote to. The previous body of unconditional regex/`str.replace` calls — which left an already-migrated tree corrupted with duplicate dataclass fields and a broken `return HookProfile(...)` block when re-run — is replaced by an idempotent rename: `apply_field_renames` is pure string-in/string-out, `migrate_file` only writes when the produced text differs from disk and reports `existed`/`changed`, missing files report `existed=False` without raising, and `apply_hook_rewrites(root)` walks `HOOK_TARGET_FILES` in declared order returning one `HookRewriteResult` per target. `main()` prints a `rewrote`/`unchanged`/`missing` line per result and exits 0; `if __name__ == "__main__"` is preserved. `tests/test_rewrite_hook_depth.py` pins canonical-rename, idempotency, write-on-change, no-op-on-migrated-file, missing-file handling, declared-order tree migration, end-to-end idempotency on a migrated tree, the canonical rename table, and fractal depth >= 2; senseweave hook tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:305:- Added depth-2 trust manager planning (frac-0038): `promptclaw/coherence/trust.py` now exposes a frozen `TrustEventPlan` plus `trust_event_plans()` returning the canonical `hard_violation`, `soft_violation`, and `compliant_action` plans sourced from `TrustManager.HARD_PENALTY`, `SOFT_PENALTY`, and `COMPLIANT_REWARD`. `TrustManager.apply_event(agent, plan)` is the single mutation path — it validates the counter field against the canonical set, clamps the new score to `[0.0, 1.0]`, increments the named counter, touches the timestamp, and returns the new score. The legacy `apply_hard_violation`, `apply_soft_violation`, and `apply_compliant_action` methods now route through `apply_event` with the canonical plans so existing penalty/reward and clamp behavior is preserved. `apply_event_by_name`, `restricted_agents`, `summarize_agent`, and `fleet_summary` give operator surfaces a JSON-safe report with the configured constants, restriction threshold, alphabetically-ordered per-agent rows, and restricted-agent count. `tests/test_trust_depth.py` pins the canonical plan, apply-event routing, legacy-method delegation, JSON-safe sorted summary, unknown-counter rejection, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_trust.py` remains the regression anchor for existing penalty/reward, clamping, restriction-threshold, and multi-agent isolation behavior.
CHANGELOG.md:309:- Added depth-2 Theramini MIDI listener (frac-0036): `my-claw/tools/theramini_midi.py` is now import-safe and exposes typed helpers `midi_to_freq`, `midi_to_name`, `parse_midi_messages`, `apply_midi_event`, `process_buffer`, `render_state`, `write_state`, `read_midi_buffer`, `process_once`, and `run_daemon` plus frozen `MidiEvent` and mutable `MidiState` dataclasses that hold the current note, last-note timestamp, silence-start timestamp, CC map, and pitch-bend value. The listener parses raw Note On / Note Off / CC / pitch-bend bytes (including the velocity-zero Note On = Note Off and 2-byte program/channel-pressure cases), folds events into a per-cycle `MidiState`, and atomically writes `/tmp/theramini_state.json` with the existing consumer contract (`timestamp`, `is_playing`, `pitch_hz`, `pitch_note`, `pitch_confidence`, `state`, `consecutive_silence_ms`, `midi_cc`, `pitch_bend`) after passing through `senseweave.theramini_duet.normalize_theramini_state` so the duet conversation contract is preserved. `is_playing` decays to `False` after `2.0` seconds without a fresh note. Loop control gains `--device`, `--interval`, `--state-path`, `--once`, and `--max-iterations`; missing or unopenable MIDI devices fall back to the existing `state="no_device"` payload shape. `tests/test_theramini_midi.py` pins import safety, MIDI parse/apply, active-note and silent-window rendering, end-to-end fd writes, and the no-device fallback; `tests/test_theramini_listener_runtime.py`, `tests/test_theramini_duet.py`, and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
