CHANGELOG.md:353:- Added depth-2 production course helpers (frac-0014): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/production_course.py` now exposes frozen `CourseSummary`, `ChapterDigest`, `ArcPhaseSnapshot`, and `CourseArcPlan` dataclasses plus pure helpers `summarize_course`, `chapter_digest`, `catalog_digest`, `arc_phase_snapshot`, `arc_phase_snapshots`, `course_titles`, `plan_course_arc`, and `validate_course` so runtime diagnostics and tests can render an operator-readable view of a section course (chapter count, transition type, mix role, resolved concept titles in declared chapter order), digest each chapter with its first three sample concept values, snapshot every required arc phase with a `sparse` / `balanced` / `dense` density bucket, plan an arc end-to-end by reusing `course_for_section` across a sequence of section descriptors with the last transition cleanly resolving to `terminal`, and report unknown-value chapters as a sorted tuple. Existing `REQUIRED_CHAPTER_IDS`, `REQUIRED_PHASE_NAMES`, `COURSE_CHAPTERS`, `ARC_PHASE_PROFILES`, `load_course_chapters`, `load_arc_phase_profiles`, `course_chapter`, `course_concept`, `arc_phase_profile`, `transition_type_for_section`, and `course_for_section` semantics are preserved so the score-tree composer and `tests/test_production_course_knowledge_base.py` / `tests/test_production_course_integration.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_production_course_depth.py` pins summary title order, chapter digest metadata + `KeyError` on unknown ids, catalog digest coverage, density bucketing + `KeyError` on unknown phase, end-to-end arc plan + empty short-circuit, and validator behavior, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:357:- Added depth-2 genre literacy helpers (frac-0012): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/genre_literacy.py` now exposes frozen `GenreSummary` / `GenreBlend` dataclasses plus pure helpers `summarize_strategy`, `genre_compatibility`, `blend_genre_strategies`, and `recommend_genre_sequence` so cast-planner, mix, and operator-diagnostics callers can render a stable per-genre summary (label, tempo range, texture density, chromatic tolerance, voice count, dominant grooves, top arc phases, calm/balanced/intense mood bucket), score a bounded `[0.0, 1.0]` symmetric compatibility between two traditions from arc-affinity cosine, modal/groove Jaccard ratios, and texture/chromatic distance, blend numeric hints with a clamped `[0.0, 1.0]` weight (tempo range, texture density, chromatic tolerance, rubato tolerance, repetition tolerance, spatial width, sorted shared modal preferences), and plan one genre per supplied arc phase with rolling fatigue from prior selections. Existing `GenreStrategy`/`REQUIRED_GENRES` data, `strategy_for_genre`, `all_strategies`, `genre_arc_affinity`, `best_genres_for_phase`, and `select_genre` semantics are preserved; `tests/test_genre_literacy_depth.py` pins summary stability and mood bucketing, compatibility self-identity / symmetry / boundedness with related-vs-contrasted ranking, blend interpolation / clamp / modal intersection, sequence per-phase coverage with no immediate repeats, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:365:- Added depth-2 commission context helpers (frac-0008): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/commission_context.py` now exposes a frozen `CommissionInputs` dataclass plus pure helpers `attention_pressure_from_world`, `commission_inputs_from_tracker_plan`, and `summarize_commission_context` so duet-composer / score-tree callers can resolve the full set of inputs `commission_piece` consumes (cadence, occupancy, day/weekly phase, attention score, narrative pressure, song number, hour) and render an operator-readable diagnostic snapshot without re-deriving the `getattr` plumbing inline. `attention_pressure_from_world` clamps `attention_score` and `experimentation_bias` into `[0.0, 1.0]` and treats `None` / non-numeric inputs as `0.0`; `summarize_commission_context` buckets attention into `low` (<0.33) / `moderate` (<0.66) / `high` and rounds narrative pressure to three decimals so log lines stay stable across small sensor jitters. The existing `commission_context_from_tracker_plan(tracker_plan, world)` keyword-only signature and `(day_phase, weekly_phase)` return contract are preserved (now walking sources with whitespace stripping and only defaulting `day_phase` to `"day"`), so `duet_composer._build_score_tree_piece` and `tests/test_commission_context.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_commission_context_depth.py` pins tracker→world→default fallback, unit-interval clamping, malformed-input handling, full-bundle population, default-occupancy fallback, and the snapshot's bucketed attention plus rounded pressure shape, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors for `bootstrap_identity()` ordering.
CHANGELOG.md:371:- Added depth-2 archive path layout helpers (frac-0005): `my-claw/tools/archive_paths.py` now exposes `ArchivePathLayout`, `resolve_archive_layout`, `archive_layout_summary`, and `prepare_archive_layout` so archive daemon outputs, rendered sample events, camera capture rings, and Litestream backups can be resolved and prepared as one typed storage layout while preserving the existing resolver functions. Regression coverage in `tests/test_archive_paths.py` pins root-source metadata, summary output, directory creation, legacy resolver compatibility, and fractal depth >= 2.
CHANGELOG.md:377:- Added depth-2 X11 gallery wrapper helpers (frac-0002): `my-claw/tools/gallery_x11.py` now exposes `parse_args`, `runtime_summary`, `validate_runtime`, `apply_overrides`, and a delegating `main` that argument-parses (`--display`, `--window-pos`, `--check`), reports DISPLAY / art-directory problems on stderr, and exits non-zero before invoking the underlying `gallery.gallery_x11.main()` when the runtime is unhealthy. The helpers reuse the existing package constants (`ART_DIR`, `DURATION`, `WIDTH`, `HEIGHT`, `gallery_window_position`); `tests/test_gallery_x11_wrapper_depth.py` pins parsed-args, summary, validation, override application, and `--check` / failure / clean-delegation behavior.
CHANGELOG.md:379:- Added a stdlib-only narrative API smoke CLI (T-016@20260502T001347Za): `scripts/smoke_narrative.py` reads the base URL from `--base-url` or `NARRATIVE_BASE_URL` (defaulting to `http://cypherclaw:8765`), performs `GET /health` against `cypherclaw.narrative_api`, prints status code plus a 200-char body preview, and exits non-zero on any non-2xx response or connection failure. The optional `--token` flag is sent as the `X-Narrative-Auth` shared-secret header that the API enforces when `NARRATIVE_AUTH_TOKEN` is set, so the Deniable operator can validate the service from their Mac over Tailscale without a virtualenv. Documented in `README.md`; regression coverage in `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` pins the success path, non-2xx exit, unreachable-host exit, header propagation, and body truncation.
CHANGELOG.md:383:- Added the CypherClaw narrative entity mutation endpoint (T-015@20260502T001347Z): `PATCH /world/entities/{entity_id}` now accepts either a wrapped `{"mutations": [...]}` body or a single integration-spec `StateMutation` object, applies `set`, `increment`, `decrement`, `append`, and `remove` against entity `properties` paths, validates optional `target_entity` against the path ID, and persists the updated entity through duck-typed deploy-side store methods (`update_entity`/`patch_entity`/`save_entity`/`upsert_entity`/`record_entity`). The route returns the updated `EntityRecord`, surfaces missing entities as `404`, missing stores as `503`, validation failures as `422`, and downstream persistence failures as `502`. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py` pins the fighter `current_state` healthy-to-wounded round trip, numeric/list/nested mutation semantics, single-mutation payload compatibility, invalid-mutation no-persist behavior, missing entity/store handling, downstream failure handling, and shared-secret auth behavior.
CHANGELOG.md:385:- Added the CypherClaw narrative entity creation endpoint (T-014@20260502T001347Z): `POST /world/entities` now accepts `{type, name, domain, properties}`, validates `domain` against the `{shared, cypherclaw, deniable}` whitelist before touching the store, and routes through a new `create_world_entity(...)` helper that duck-types the deploy-side world store across `create_entity`/`add_entity`/`record_entity`/`upsert_entity`/`save_entity` (kwarg-shaped or single-mapping signatures). The route returns HTTP `201` with the store-assigned ID populated through the shared entity normalization pipeline so the new entity is immediately re-fetchable via `GET /world/entities/{entity_id}`, falls back to the request input for `type`/`name`/`domain`/`properties` when the store returns a partial record, and surfaces HTTP `502` when the store returns no ID, `503` when no store can be constructed, and `422` for whitelist/empty-string violations. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py` pins the squad-member round trip via GET, each whitelisted domain, blank/missing-input rejection, downstream-failure handling, missing-store fallback, partial-record fallback, no-ID surfacing, the record-dict signature path, and shared-secret auth behavior.
CHANGELOG.md:387:- Added the CypherClaw narrative beat endpoint (T-011@20260502T001347Z): `POST /beats/next` now validates `{cycle_number, domain_filter, arc_position_target?, force_arc_event?}`, wraps an injected or lazily imported deploy-side `NarrativeEngine.next_beat()`, preserves the engine-owned serialized `StoryBeat` JSON shape without padding absent fields, and returns clear `503` unavailable / `502` generation-failure errors. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_beats.py` pins parameter passing, raw mapping shape preservation, dataclass/nested serialization, validation-before-engine behavior, downstream failure handling, missing-engine fallback, and shared-secret auth behavior.
CHANGELOG.md:389:- Added the CypherClaw narrative API regression suite plus a minimal auth gate (T-005@20260502T001347Z): `cypherclaw.narrative_api.create_app(...)` now accepts an optional `auth_token` keyword that, when set, requires every endpoint to carry a matching `X-Narrative-Auth` header (missing/wrong → 401); empty/unset preserves the existing auth-disabled behavior so T-010's env-var pull and startup warning land cleanly. `tests/test_narrative_api_memory.py` and `tests/test_narrative_api_events.py` now pin the four scenario floors (success path, auth failure when enabled, bad input validation, downstream-engine error handling) for `POST /memory/search`, `GET /events`, and `POST /events`, plus 503 fallback behavior when the deploy-side `cypherclaw.narrative.{memory,events}` package is absent and append-returns-None record synthesis. `pytest --cov=cypherclaw.narrative_api` reports 84% module coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:391:- Added the CypherClaw narrative event append HTTP slice (T-003@20260502T001347Z): `POST /events` now accepts narrative events such as `raid.completed`, defaults omitted domains to `shared`, appends through the same injectable/lazy deploy-side event-store wrapper used by `GET /events`, normalizes the created event record, and returns downstream append failures as HTTP 502. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_events.py` pins raid-outcome persistence, read-after-write through `GET /events`, shared-domain defaults, validation, and downstream error handling.
CHANGELOG.md:393:- Added the CypherClaw narrative memory search HTTP slice (T-001@20260502T001347Z): new `cypherclaw.narrative_api` exposes `POST /memory/search` through a FastAPI `create_app(...)` factory, wraps deploy-side `NarrativeMemory` via lazy import, supports injected memory searchers for tests, normalizes common result shapes into ranked `{id, text, similarity, domain, metadata}` responses, and defensively honors `domain_filter` for shared/Deniable/CypherClaw memory separation. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_memory.py` pins ranking, domain filtering, single-domain requests, validation, and downstream failure handling.
CHANGELOG.md:397:- Added an operator runbook for the generation backend (T-011): new `docs/runbooks/generation-backend.md` documents how to check generation status, widen/tighten the daily and monthly USD budget caps (`CYPHERCLAW_GENERATION_DAILY_CAP_USD` default `5.0`, `CYPHERCLAW_GENERATION_MONTHLY_CAP_USD` default `100.0`), switch between Replicate / Modal / local backends, roll back the IDyOM long-term model from the immutable week-0 snapshot when the weekly collapse audit fires, clear stuck `running` rows from `/home/user/cypherclaw-data/generation_queue.db`, inspect the LRU cache at `/home/user/cypherclaw-data/cache/`, and find generated audio (`samples/generated/<YYYY-MM-DD>/<request_hash>.wav`) and journals (`/home/user/cypherclaw-data/state/sensory_journal.jsonl`, `samples/usage_journal.jsonl`). The runbook documents every env var the generation system reads (`CYPHERCLAW_GENERATION_DAILY_CAP_USD`, `CYPHERCLAW_GENERATION_MONTHLY_CAP_USD`, `IDYOM_KL_AUDIT_CONFIG`, `REPLICATE_API_TOKEN`, `MODAL_TOKEN_ID`, `MODAL_TOKEN_SECRET`) with defaults, calls out that all rollovers are UTC, links the canonical `sdp/telemetry/cost-model.md` and `idyom_kl_audit_config.json.example`, and includes five worked debugging scenarios (cap breach, wedged `running` row, cold cache, collapse alert rollback, Replicate→Modal failover). Locked against drift by `tests/test_runbook_generation_backend.py`, which pins the runbook's title style, required workflow coverage, env-var documentation, exactly-five `### Scenario N` headings, and on-disk path / cross-link integrity.
CHANGELOG.md:401:- Added a steady-state SDP cost extractor and committed CSV (T-032@b): `promptclaw/sdp_cost.py` exposes `TOKEN_PRICING`, `match_pricing`, `call_cost_usd`, `DailyCostRow`, `extract_steady_state_cost`, and `write_csv`, applying the substring-matched pricing table from `sdp/telemetry/cost-model.md` (claude-opus-4 $15/$75, claude-sonnet-4 $3/$15, claude-haiku $0.80/$4, gpt-4o $2.50/$10, o3 $10/$40, codex-mini $1.50/$6, fallback $3/$15) to per-task `lead_profile_id` rows in the `.sdp/state.db` `telemetry` table. The CLI `python -m promptclaw.sdp_cost --db .sdp/state.db --days 7 --out sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cost.csv` rolls the 7 most recent active UTC days into the committed `sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cost.csv` (header `date,runs,input_tokens,output_tokens,cache_creation_tokens,cache_read_tokens,total_cost_usd,models`); `cache_creation_tokens`, `cache_read_tokens`, and `thinking_tokens` are reported but not billed, matching the cost-model.md formula. Test coverage in `tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py` pins the pricing table values, substring-and-fallback matching, the cost-model.md worked example (`(in/1e6*in_p)+(out/1e6*out_p)`), per-day grouping with sorted unique tier lists, the locked CSV header schema with 4-decimal USD formatting and `|`-joined models, and the CLI's stdout path echo.
CHANGELOG.md:405:- Added a weekly KL-divergence audit between the current IDyOM long-term model and an immutable week-0 snapshot (T-031): new `senseweave.generation.health.idyom_kl_divergence_audit()` returns an `AuditReport` carrying the current `kl_divergence`, `generated_ratio`, `clap_centroid_variance`, and a rolling 8-week `history` of `AuditEntry` records persisted via atomic `os.replace` at `/home/user/cypherclaw-data/state/idyom_kl_audit.json`. KL is symmetric (`0.5*(KL(P||Q)+KL(Q||P))`) over a Laplace-smoothed (`alpha=1.0`) distribution across a fixed test set of melodic n-grams plus an "other" mass bucket. Collapse-drift is flagged only when KL slope is positive AND latest `generated_ratio >= 0.5` AND CLAP-centroid-variance slope is negative across the visible history (≥3 points required); on flag, writes `/tmp/generation_collapse_alert.json` and never auto-rollbacks the LTM. Ships with `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-idyom-kl-audit.{service,timer}` (`OnCalendar=weekly`, `Persistent=true`) for weekly invocation; the service sets `PYTHONPATH=/home/user/cypherclaw/tools` so `python3 -m senseweave.generation.health` resolves and points `IDYOM_KL_AUDIT_CONFIG` at a JSON config alongside the new `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/idyom_kl_audit_config.json.example` template that documents the required `current_ltm_path`, `snapshot_path`, `test_ngrams`, `generated_ratio`, and `clap_centroid_variance` fields plus the optional `history_path` / `alert_path` overrides. Test coverage in `tests/test_generation_health.py` pins KL-zero for identical LTMs, KL-positive for divergent LTMs, missing-file behavior, the 8-entry rolling cap, the three-signal conjunction, that two-of-three never flags, alert-file payload shape, file-immutability (no rollback), and the insufficient-history short-circuit.
CHANGELOG.md:411:- Added a live Replicate smoke test for the generation backend (T-005): `tests/test_generation_live_replicate.py` exercises `ReplicateClient.generate(req)` against the real Replicate API with a fixed prompt and seed, and asserts a >100 KB WAV payload, `cost_usd` inside `[$0.01, $0.50]`, and `latency_ms < 60000`. The test is gated behind both the new `--run-live-replicate` pytest flag (registered in `tests/conftest.py` alongside the existing `--run-live-modal` seam) and a non-empty `REPLICATE_API_TOKEN`, so the default `pytest tests/` run skips it. Documented as ~$0.10 per opted-in run.
CHANGELOG.md:413:- Added a local Ada generation backend stub: `senseweave.generation.client_local.LocalAdaClient` now satisfies the shared `GenerationClient` Protocol shape while raising `NotImplementedError("LocalAdaClient: GPU not yet installed; use Replicate or Modal")` until the local GPU path is installed. Added focused tests and an explicit mypy check for Protocol satisfaction.
CHANGELOG.md:415:- Implemented `ModalClient` satisfying `GenerationClient` Protocol in `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_modal.py`, enabling CypherClaw to use Modal serverless for generation (CCG-012). The client computes A10G runtime cost from metadata and gracefully degrades when the `modal` SDK is not installed. Also added protocol parity tests and gated live Modal tests behind `--run-live-modal`.
CHANGELOG.md:450:- Implemented ST1-ST6 of the score-tree songwriting stack end to end: added `piece_commission.py`, `piece_brief.py`, `form_grammar.py`, `score_tree.py`, `recursive_composer.py`, `composition_gate.py`, `tracker_compiler.py`, and `piece_queue.py`; extended `repertoire_memory.py` to store structural score-tree summaries; and rewired `duet_composer.py` so tracker solo mode can commission a piece, build a complete score tree, gate it, compile it into tracker scenes, and precompose the next piece into a small persistent queue instead of treating the tracker as the composer.
CHANGELOG.md:462:- Added arrangement automation curves to tracker playback: `music_tracker.py` now derives `arrangement_curve` from section rhythm, writes row-point automation for `density`, `master_amp`, and `reverb_send`, shapes note velocity across each lane's active window, and `music_tracker_runtime.py` / `duet_composer.py` now expose and apply interpolated automation to the live master bus during the section. Low density also thins optional color/counter runtime events while preserving melody and bass continuity.
CHANGELOG.md:511:- Fed EMSD production plans into actual tracker playback: added `emsd_performance.py`, wired `duet_composer.py` to apply live mix/sample/DSP adjustments at the note boundary, extended `composer_emsd_extras()` with concrete sample capture metadata, and made the strongest top register fold down harder so notes above roughly `C6` are lowered an octave and the sharpest band is lowered two octaves.
CHANGELOG.md:545:- Added explicit runtime voice aliases so unavailable or unsafe voices can degrade cleanly: `grain` now resolves to `breath`, and `tabla_ge` currently resolves to `tabla_tin` until a real `sw_tabla_ge` SynthDef is deployed.
CHANGELOG.md:549:- Added a concrete CypherClaw upgrade checklist covering phase status, owned files, test gates, and live deployment order for the presence/cadence/personality/audio-efficiency program.
CHANGELOG.md:581:- Removed backup-restore and ad hoc pipeline-start behavior from `boot_hardening.sh` so runtime authority stays with the managed bootstrap and runner path.
