sdp/verification/t-036@20260515t214233z-verify.md:39:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-05-16T05:15:56.312Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1778908556312_1","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-036 @sdp/logs/Verify_T-036_20260515T214233Z_1778908510.log\n\n**Verify Agent:** gemini-3-flash-preview\n**Date:** Saturday, May 16, 2026\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `promptclaw/pal_agent.py`\n- `promptclaw/cli.py`\n- `tests/test_pal_agent.py`\n- Git history (commits `baa8358`, `8d72a21`)\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation correctly identifies and rejects action IDs that are unknown to the action registry. This is enforced at two levels:\n1.  **CLI Level**: The `pal-agent approve` command compares requested action IDs against the `proposed_actions` in the saved plan. Since unknown actions are filtered out during plan generation, any unknown ID provided to `approve` is rejected.\n2.  **Agent Logic Level**: In `run_pal_ops_actions`, `ignored_approvals` explicitly includes any `action_id` that is not in the `actions` registry or not in the `proposed_set`.\n\n## Completeness\nThe test case `test_pal_ops_actions_unknown_approved_ids_never_reach_action_runner` comprehensively covers the following scenarios:\n- An action ID that is in the plan but unknown to the registry (e.g., due to a mismatch or missing capability).\n- An action ID that is neither in the plan nor the registry.\n- Verification that valid actions still execute correctly alongside unknown ones.\n- Verification that unknown actions never reach the action runner.\n\n## Consistency\nThe changes follow the established patterns for PAL agent action handling and the use of the `ignored_approvals` list to track rejected inputs.\n\n## Security\nThis change provides a critical security boundary by ensuring that the agent cannot be tricked into executing arbitrary action IDs that weren't part of its validated registry or the specific proposed plan.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is clean, and the test is well-structured with clear assertions. The use of defense-in-depth (CLI rejection + Agent logic filtering) is a high-quality approach.\n\n## Issues Found\nNone.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid. The combination of T-035 and T-036 provides robust protection against unauthorized or unknown action execution.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-036 @20260515t214233z-verify.md"}}
