sdp/verification/t-015@20260425t183959zd-verify.md:11:{"type":"message","timestamp":"2026-04-26T00:46:55.135Z","role":"user","content":"# Verification: Task T-015@20260425T183959Zd\n\n**Task:** Wire fixtures into CI: add fast unit-test job running the detector-branch smoke test, ensure runtime <30s, and document fixture regeneration in tests/fixtures/audio/README.\n**Tier:** T1\n\nYou are the VERIFY agent for this task. The LEAD agent has completed their work.\n\n\n## Review Checklist\n\n1. **Review recent commits:**\n   ```bash\n   git log --oneline -5\n   git diff HEAD~3 --stat\n   ```\n\n2. **Review code changes:**\n   ```bash\n   git diff HEAD~3\n   ```\n\n4. **Check ESCALATIONS.md** for any flagged issues.\n\n5. **Run the test suite:**\n   ```bash\n   pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x\n   ```\n\n## Evaluation Criteria\n\nEvaluate the work against these five dimensions:\n\n1. **Correctness**: Does the output match the requirements/spec?\n2. **Completeness**: Are there gaps, missing edge cases, or unhandled scenarios?\n3. **Consistency**: Does the output follow established patterns and conventions?\n4. **Security**: Are there vulnerabilities, leaked secrets, or unsafe practices?\n5. **Quality**: Does the output meet the quality gates for this phase?\n\n## Output\n\nWrite your verification report and all findings to this exact path:\n`sdp/verification/t-015@20260425t183959zd-verify.md`\nDo not use a different filename or directory.\n\nUse this format:\n\n```markdown\n# Verification Report — T-015@20260425T183959Zd\n\n**Verify Agent:** [your agent name]\n**Date:** [today]\n**Artifacts Reviewed:** [list files reviewed]\n\n## Correctness\n[assessment]\n\n## Completeness\n[assessment]\n\n## Consistency\n[assessment]\n\n## Security\n[assessment]\n\n## Quality\n[assessment]\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] [Issue — severity: blocking/minor]\n\n## Verdict: [PASS | PASS WITH NOTES | FAIL]\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\n[specific items to address]\n```\n\nCommit the verification report.\n\n## Candidate Hardening (Auto-Generated)\n\nUse the recurring failure patterns below as mandatory hardening checks:\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Runtime does not invoke bootstrap_identity on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at first run. Severity: blocking.\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Add bootstrap_identity() invocation in startup flow (before FirstBootAnnouncer) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Ensure this path is used on both standalone and federated modes..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Add an integration test that exercises startup and verifies identity persistence between boots..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Re-run pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x after wiring the startup path..\n"}
sdp/verification/t-015@20260425t183959zd-verify.md:20:{"type":"tool_result","timestamp":"2026-04-26T00:47:02.337Z","tool_id":"run_shell_command_1777164422152_0","status":"success","output":"name: detector-branch-smoke\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [\"**\"]\n  pull_request:\n\njobs:\n  detector-branch-smoke:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    timeout-minutes: 5\n\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - name: Set up Python\n        uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n        with:\n          python-version: \"3.11\"\n          cache: pip\n\n      - name: Install package + dev extras\n        run: |\n          python -m pip install --upgrade pip\n          pip install -e '.[dev]'\n\n      - name: Detector-branch smoke test (canned WAV fixtures, <30s)\n        run: |\n          # Wall-clock guard: the smoke job must finish in <30s.\n          timeout 30 python -m pytest \\\n            tests/test_sample_capture_daemon.py \\\n            -k \"fixture or smoke\" \\\n            -x --tb=short --durations=10\n# Canned audio fixtures\n\nDeterministic 1-second mono 16-bit PCM WAV files at 8 kHz, used by the\ndetector-branch smoke test in `tests/test_sample_capture_daemon.py` to\nexercise `InterestingMomentDetector` without depending on JACK or live\ncapture.\n\n| Fixture | Detector branch | Seed |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `silence.wav` | baseline; must not flag | — |\n| `dishwasher.wav` | steady hum baseline; must not flag | 7 |\n| `footsteps.wav` | broadband transients | 11 |\n| `music.wav` | tonal pad + plucks | (deterministic) |\n| `dogs.wav` | bark-style tonal bursts | 17 |\n| `transient_cluster.wav` | dense transient cluster | 23 |\n\n## Regenerating the fixtures\n\nThe generator lives next to the WAVs at `generate.py`. It uses fixed RNG\nseeds, so the bytes on disk are reproducible across machines as long as\nNumPy's `default_rng` stream is stable.\n\n```bash\npython tests/fixtures/audio/generate.py\n```\n\nThat rewrites every fixture in this directory in place. To refresh only\none fixture, edit its generator function (e.g. `dogs()`) and rerun the\nscript — non-edited fixtures regenerate to identical bytes.\n\n## When to regenerate\n\n- The synthesis parameters in `generate.py` change (frequencies,\n  envelopes, burst counts, durations).\n- `SAMPLE_RATE` or `DURATION_SECONDS` change.\n- A new detector branch needs a dedicated fixture (add a generator,\n  register it in `FIXTURES`, rerun, then add a parametrize case in\n  `test_detector_branch_smoke_test_flags_on_matching_fixture`).\n\nAfter regenerating, run the smoke test locally before committing:\n\n```bash\npytest tests/test_sample_capture_daemon.py -k \"fixture or smoke\"\n```\n\nThe same selector runs in the `detector-branch-smoke` GitHub Actions\njob (`.github/workflows/detector-smoke.yml`), which is wall-clock\nbounded to 30 seconds.\n\n## Format invariants\n\nAll fixtures must be mono, 16-bit PCM, 8 kHz, exactly 1 second long.\n`test_canned_fixtures_are_one_second_at_eight_kilohertz` enforces this\non every run; if it fails after a regen, check that you did not change\n`SAMPLE_RATE` or `DURATION_SECONDS` without updating the test.\n# Escalations\n\nItems requiring human review. Append-only per task.\n\n## T-001 (2026-04-01T18:55:24.984659+00:00)\n\n- **Reason:** Agent timeout\n- **Details:** T-001 timed out twice. Run sdp-cli tasks split T-001 to break it down.\n\n## T-001 (2026-04-01T18:56:11.434931+00:00)\n\n- **Reason:** Agent timeout\n- **Details:** T-001 timed out twice. Run sdp-cli tasks split T-001 to break it down.\n\n## T-001 (2026-04-01T18:56:41.692113+00:00)\n\n- **Reason:** Agent timeout\n- **Details:** T-001 timed out twice. Run sdp-cli tasks split T-001 to break it down.\n\n## T-009@20260408T220341Z (2026-04-08T22:12:54.185469+00:00)\n\n- **Reason:** Ordered degradation policy\n- **Details:** step-1: reason=verify-first tier cascade: promoted verify-tier model as lead; original_pair=claude->codex; degraded_pair=codex->claude; remaining_headroom=8